    <stitle>VT 275 Engine Diagnostics Manual - Electronic Control Systems Diagnostics - Circuit Diagnostics - BAP
        (Barometric Absolute Pressure) Sensor
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc id="s305010706.4" svcproctype="diagnose" graphiccount="4">
        <title>BAP (Barometric Absolute Pressure) Sensor</title>
        <svcprocinfo id="s305010706.4.1">
            <figure id="f305010724" figsize="pg-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figj31/J31071.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="472px" box="no"/>
                <caption>Function diagram for the BAP sensor</caption>
            </figure>
            <para id="s305010706.4.1.1"></para>
            <table id="t305010734" type="simple" frame="topbot">
                <title>The function diagram for the BAP sensor includes the following:</title>
                <tgroup cols="1">
                    <colspec colname="col1" colwidth="1.0*"/>
                    <tbody>
                        <row rowsep="0">
                            <entry>
                                <para>Barometric Absolute Pressure (BAP) sensor</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row rowsep="0">
                            <entry>
                                <para>Electronic Control Module (ECM)</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row rowsep="0">
                            <entry>
                                <para>Injection Driver Module (IDM)</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row rowsep="0">
                            <entry>
                                <para>Boost Control Solenoid (BCS) assembly</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row rowsep="0">
                            <entry>
                                <para>Fuel injector</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row rowsep="0">
                            <entry>
                                <para>Amber Lamp (Warn Engine Lamp (WEL) for CF)</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row rowsep="0">
                            <entry>
                                <para>Exhaust Gas Recirculation (EGR)</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                    </tbody>
                </tgroup>
            </table>
            <para>
                <title>Function</title>The BAP sensor is a cab mounted variable capacitance sensor. The ECM supplies a 5
                volt reference signal which the BAP sensor uses to produce a linear analog voltage signal that indicates
                pressure.
            </para>
            <para>The primary function of the BAP sensor is to provide a feedback signal to the ECM to adjust fuel
                timing and quantity. The ECM monitors the BAP signal to determine altitude, adjust fuel timing and
                quantity, glow plug operation, and air heater operation.
            </para>
        </svcprocinfo>
        <svcsubproc id="s305010706.4.2">
            <title>BAP Circuit Operation</title>
            <figure id="f305010725" figsize="pg-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figj31/J31072.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="472px"/>
                <caption>BAP circuit diagram</caption>
            </figure>
            <para>The BAP sensor is supplied with a 5 volt reference at Pin 2 from ECM Pin X4-4 . The BAP sensor is
                grounded at Pin 1 from ECM Pin X4-24. The BAP sensor returns a variable voltage signal from Pin 3 to ECM
                at Pin X3-24.
            </para>
            <para>
                <title>Fault Detection/Management</title>When the ECM detects the BAP voltage signal out of range high
                or low, the ECM will ignore the BAP signal and use the Manifold Absolute Pressure (MAP) signal generated
                at low idle as an indication of barometric pressure. When a MAP fault is detected, the BAP signal will
                default to barometric pressure at sea level, 100.24 kPa (29.6 in Hg).
            </para>
            <para>
                <title>BAP DTCs</title>DTCs are read using the EST or by counting the flashes from the amber and red
                lamps.
            </para>
            <table id="t305010735" tblwidth="col-wide" type="simple" frame="topbot">
                <title>DTC 151</title>
                <tgroup cols="1" align="left">
                    <colspec colname="col1" colwidth="1.0*"/>
                    <tbody>
                        <row>
                            <entry>
                                <para>BAP signal out of range high</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row rowsep="0">
                            <entry>
                                <para>DTC 151 is set when the BAP signal is greater than 4.95 volts for more than 0.5
                                    second.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row rowsep="0">
                            <entry>
                                <para>DTC 151 can be set when the signal circuit is shorted to V
                                    <subscript>REF</subscript>
                                    or B+ or a failed BAP sensor.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row rowsep="0">
                            <entry>
                                <para>When DTC 151 is active the amber lamp (WEL for CF) is illuminated.</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                    </tbody>
                </tgroup>
            </table>
            <figure id="f305010726" figsize="pg-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figj31/J31072.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="472px"/>
                <caption>BAP circuit diagram</caption>
            </figure>
            <table id="t305010736" tblwidth="col-wide" type="simple" frame="topbot">
                <title>DTC 152</title>
                <tgroup cols="1" align="left">
                    <colspec colname="col1" colwidth="1.0*"/>
                    <tbody>
                        <row>
                            <entry>
                                <para>BAP signal out of range low</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row rowsep="0">
                            <entry>
                                <para>DTC 152 is set when the BAP signal is less than 1.0 volt for more than 0.5
                                    seconds.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row rowsep="0">
                            <entry>
                                <para>DTC 152 can be set when the signal circuit is shorted to ground or open. If the V
                                    <subscript>REF</subscript>
                                    is shorted to ground, DTC 152 can be set. A failed BAP sensor can set DTC 152.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row rowsep="0">
                            <entry>
                                <para>When DTC 152 is active the amber lamp (WEL for CF) is illuminated.</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                    </tbody>
                </tgroup>
            </table>
            <para></para>
            <table id="t305010737" type="simple" frame="topbot">
                <title>Tools</title>
                <tgroup cols="1">
                    <colspec colname="col1" colwidth="1.0*"/>
                    <tbody>
                        <row rowsep="0">
                            <entry>
                                <para>EST with MasterDiagnostics&#174; software</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row rowsep="0">
                            <entry>
                                <para>EZ-Tech&#174; interface cable</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row rowsep="0">
                            <entry>
                                <para>Digital Multimeter (DMM)</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row rowsep="0">
